node.title: NT COVID-19 hospitalisations jump to 32, as Territory records equal daily record of 594 new cases
node.alt: Northern Territory Chief Minister Michael Gunner speaking at a press conference in Parliament House.
node.description: The Northern Territory recorded 594 new coronavirus cases overnight, with 32 people in hospital and two in intensive care.
node.content: ["The number of people with COVID-19 in Northern Territory\u00a0hospitals has climbed to 32, a jump on yesterday's total of 26, Deputy Chief Minister Nicole Manison has announced.", "Of those, two patients are in ICU, though only one of those\u00a0is there due to COVID-19.", "The NT has recorded 594 new COVID-19 cases in the past 24 hours, taking the total number of active cases in the Territory to 2,600.", "More to come."]
